sentences: Nathalie Loriers (born 27 October 1966, Namur) is a Belgian jazz pianist and composer.
In 1991 Loriers formed her own quartet with Kurt Van Herck (saxophone), Philippe Aerts (double bass) and Mimi Verderame (drums).
She won the 1999 Golden Django for best French-speaking artist.
Belga Prize, Brussels Jazz Rally, Best Soloist, 1990
EuroDjango Award, Contemporary European Jazz Artist, 2000
Bobby Jaspar Prize, Académie du Jazz, 2000
Walking Through Walls, Walking Along Walls (Igloo, 1995)
